# Project Workflow

## Before writing code

- If the user asks for a new feature or screen, propose a short plan first unless they say "just do it."
- Plans must include: screens, data models, and what is explicitly OUT of scope for v1.
- Do not scaffold the project with `create-expo-app` — the user runs that manually.

## Scope

- Prefer v1: local storage, no auth, no payments, 1–2 core features.
- Warn if the request adds auth, payments, or backend before v1 works on device.
- One feature at a time when possible.

## Before big changes

- Ask before deleting files, renaming routes, or refactoring more than 3 files.
- Match the approved plan in AGENTS.md or PLAN.md if present.

## Context

- If conversation is long or confused, suggest starting a new chat after updating AGENTS.md.
- Never put API keys or secrets in source files — use `.env` and `.gitignore`.

## Testing

- Remind user to run `npx expo start` and test on Expo Go after UI changes.
- When fixing bugs, ask for terminal errors or screenshots if not provided.
